translated: Ysander, Bengt Daniel, vicar, Kungsbacka, b. 9/1/90 in Tölö, Halland county, son of vicar Bengt Y. and Amanda Wetterqvist. Married on 18th with Anna-Lisa Bergström. — Graduated from upper secondary school in Gothenburg in 1910, graduated with a Bachelor of Theology in 1911, completed practical theology examinations in Uppsala in 1915, ordained as a priest in Gothenburg in 1916. Assistant vicar in Gällstad in 1916, Ljungby in 1916, pastor and chaplain in Seglora from 1916 to 1918, curate in Holsljunga from 1918 to 1933, vicar in Kungsbacka and Hanhals since 1933. Chairman of the city council since 1939, chairman of the church council, church assembly, church meeting, board of elementary education, RK's Kungsbacka district, member of the board of Katrinebergs folk high school since 1939, inspector of the secondary school since 1944. Awarded LVO (Order of Vasa) in 1940.
